description.narrative: (Haiti): The Kore Lavi program will continue to reduce food insecurity and vulnerability by supporting the GOH in establishing a replicable safety net system and expanding capacities to prevent child undernutrition. With FY19 funds, Kore Lavi will continue to target vulnerable households and provide food vouchers to 17,300 beneficiary households, approximately 86,000 individuals in 5 departments (18 communes). Those vouchers will be used to purchase locally-produced foods through community vendors. This program will also continue to support the development of a vulnerability mapping tool and beneficiary tracking system, which will help demonstrate how the GOH could implement a predictable, transparent social transfer system aimed at the most vulnerable in the country.
